# Calculating number of unique x_data along the streamwise direction(x_direction)

row_num = data.shape[0]   # Returns the number of rows
print(row_num)

x_dataset = pd.DataFrame(columns=['unique_x_coordinate'])
i=0

for n in range(row_num):
    if n < (row_num-1):
         if data['x_coordinate'].values[n] != data['x_coordinate'].values[n+1]:
                x_dataset.loc[i,"unique_x_coordinate"] = data['x_coordinate'].values[n]
                i=i+1
    elif n==(row_num-1):
        x_dataset.loc[i,"unique_x_coordinate"] = data['x_coordinate'].values[row_num-1]
        
        
print(x_dataset)

In [7]:
# Calculating mixing efficiency corresponding to each unique_x_coordinate using a for loop

row_unique = x_dataset.shape[0]
print(row_unique)

Result_dataset = pd.DataFrame(columns=['x_coordinate','Mixing_efficiency(%)'])

for ii in range(row_unique):
    cal_dataset = data[x_dataset.loc[ii,"unique_x_coordinate"]==data.loc[:,"x_coordinate"]]
    cal_dataset = cal_dataset.reset_index(drop=True)
    cal_dataset_row = cal_dataset.shape[0]
    
    # Stoichiometric air fuel ratio and corrected hydrogen mass fraction
    cal_dataset['st_air_fuel_ratio'] = cal_dataset.loc[:,"f_air"]*0.0285
    
    for k in range(cal_dataset_row):
        if cal_dataset.loc[k,'f_h2'] <= cal_dataset.loc[k,'st_air_fuel_ratio']:
            cal_dataset.loc[k,'st_f_h2'] = cal_dataset.loc[k,'f_h2']
        else:
            cal_dataset.loc[k,'st_f_h2'] = cal_dataset.loc[k,'f_air']*0.0293
    
    #Finding Area
    for kk in range(cal_dataset_row):
        if kk>0 :
            cal_dataset.loc[kk,'y_difference'] = cal_dataset.loc[kk,'y_coordinate']-cal_dataset.loc[kk-1,'y_coordinate']
        elif kk==0:
            cal_dataset.loc[kk,'y_difference'] = cal_dataset.loc[kk,'y_coordinate']
            
    for m in range(cal_dataset_row):
        if m==0 :
            cal_dataset.loc[m,'dA'] = cal_dataset.loc[m,'y_difference']/2
        elif m < (cal_dataset_row - 1):
            cal_dataset.loc[m,"dA"] = (cal_dataset.loc[m,'y_difference']+cal_dataset.loc[m+1,'y_difference'])/2
        elif m == (cal_dataset_row-1) :
            cal_dataset.loc[m,'dA'] = cal_dataset.loc[m,'y_difference']/2
            
    # Integral Individual Result Data (mixing-efficiency corresponding to each x_coordinate)
    for p in range(cal_dataset_row):
        cal_dataset.loc[p,'fuel_mixing_data'] = cal_dataset.loc[p,'density']*cal_dataset.loc[p,'x_velocity']*cal_dataset.loc[p,'st_f_h2']*cal_dataset.loc[p,'dA']
    
    Mixing_efficiency_sum = cal_dataset['fuel_mixing_data'].sum()
    Mixing_efficiency = Mixing_efficiency_sum*100/fuel_mass
    
    Result_dataset.loc[ii,'x_coordinate'] = x_dataset.loc[ii,'unique_x_coordinate']
    if ii !=(row_unique-1) :
        Result_dataset.loc[ii,'Mixing_efficiency(%)'] = Mixing_efficiency
    elif ii==(row_unique-1):
        Result_dataset.loc[ii,'Mixing_efficiency(%)'] = Result_dataset.loc[ii-1,'Mixing_efficiency(%)']
    
    # printing the calculated_dataset and mixing_efficiency corresponding to unique_x_coordinate
    print(cal_dataset)
    print(Mixing_efficiency)

# Plotting the final graph

# Extracting the result_dataset
x_data = Result_dataset.loc[:,'x_coordinate']
y_data = Result_dataset.loc[:,"Mixing_efficiency(%)"]

# Specifying the fonts and fontproperties for title,labels and ticks
font = {'family': ['Times New Roman'],
        'color':  'black',
        'weight': 'bold',
        'size': 14,
        }
font_tick = {
    "family":"Times New Roman",
    "size":12,
    "weight":"heavy",
    "style":"normal"
}

# Plotting the result_data
plt.plot(x_data,y_data,"r")

# Manipulating the title, labels and legend
plt.title("Mixing_efficiency_along_streamwise_location",size=15,fontweight='bold',pad=30)
plt.xlabel('Streamwise_location(x_coordinate)',fontdict=font,labelpad=15)
plt.ylabel('Mixing_efficiency(%)',fontdict=font,labelpad=15)
plt.legend(["Pressure_ratio_12"],loc="upper left",shadow=True,edgecolor='black',borderpad=0.6,prop={'weight':"normal"})

# Rearranging and specifying the ticks
plt.xticks(np.arange(0,0.200003,0.02),fontproperties=font_tick)
plt.yticks(fontproperties=font_tick)

# Specifying the limits and generating grids
plt.xlim(0,0.2)
plt.ylim(0,40)
plt.grid(True)

# Showing the plot
plt.show()
